The paper deals with theoretical frameworks and algorithms for solving cardinality constrained maximization problems, which are typically studied in the areas of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper's focus on competitive ratios and approximation ratios further supports these categories.
